.chicago_cubs_trivia_answers.description:
Chicago Cubs Trivia Answers

Which of these Cubs closers had the most saves in a playoff season?

  • Lee Smith, 1984
  • Joe Borowski, 2003
  • Mitch Williams, 1989
  • Rob Beck, 1998

Beck somehow managed to eek out 51 heart-stopping saves in 1998. Mitch "Wild Thing" Williams was second with 36. Smith and Borowski each had 33.

Of these four catchers who have started for the Cubs in the playoffs, who had the most productive offensive regular season (determined by batting average, home runs and runs batted in)? Which of these Cubs closers had the most saves in a playoff season?

  • Damen Berryhill, 1989
  • Damien Miller, 2003
  • Scott Servais, 1998
  • Jody Davis, 1984

Jody hit .256 with 19 HR and 94 RBI, clearly a stronger season than Berryhill (.257/5/41), Servais (.222/7/36,) or Miller (.233/9/36).

Of these three men who played second base for the Chicago Cubs in the playoffs, who hit the most home runs during the regular season?

  • Ryne Sandberg, 1984
  • Ryne Sandberg, 1989
  • Mickey Morandini, 1998
  • Mark Grudzielanek, 2003

Though Sandberg won the NL MVP in 1984, when he went .314/19/84, he hadn't yet developed into the home run hitter he was in 1989 (.290/30/76). Morandini and Grudzielanek hit for average rather than power (.296/8/53 and .314/3/38, respectively).

Third base has often been a trouble spot for the Cubs, but in their most successful seasons they have found a way to fill the hole. Which of these third baseman had the most home runs and runs batted in over the course of the entire regular season?

  • Gary Gaetti, 1998
  • Ron Cey, 1984
  • Aramis Ramirez, 2003
  • Vance Law, 1989

Ramirez, a mid-season acquisition from Pittsburgh, hit 27 home runs and 106 RBI in 2003, though only 15 of the home runs and 39 of the RBI were as a Cub. Ron "The Penguin" Cey was a close second with 25 HR and 97 RBI. Gaetti, another late addition, was third with 19 HR and 70 RBI of which 8 and 27 were for the Cubs after coming over from St. Louis. Vance Law had a terrible season, going .235/7/42.

Which of these Cubs left fielders hit the most home runs during a playoff season?

  • Gary Matthews, 1984
  • Moises Alou, 2003
  • Dwight Smith, 1989
  • Henry Rodriguez, 1998

"O'Henry" Rodriguez belted 31 homers to go with his .251 average and 85 RBI. Second place "Holy Moises" Alou may have had the best all around season (.280/22/91). "Sarge" Matthews was third (.291/14/82). Dwight Smith, an also-ran vote-getter in the 1989 Rookie of the Year contest won by teammate Jerome Walton, had the best batting average at .324, but only hit 9 HR with 52 RBI.

IMMEDIATE RELEASE

PERSONALIZED CUBS JERSEYS THE ULTIMATE GIFT FOR BASEBALL FANS
Preview Customized Cubs Jerseys at SportsWorldChicago.com Before You Buy

CHICAGO, IL, November 15th, 2010 - Chicago`s Sports World has been the go-to source for all Cubs merchandise since the late 1980`s, establishing itself as a true Chicago institution. Its online store, SportsWorldChicago.com, is a leading online retailer of Cubs gear and features livestream webcam footage shot from Sports World`s Wrigleyville location.

This holiday season, SportsWorldChicago.com is offering several styles of customizable jerseys. When customers choose a jersey, they can enter the name and number they`d like on the jersey. The site has also added an exciting, brand new feature this season, just in time for the holidays: the ability for customers to get a sneak peek at their customized jersey before they buy.

The Majestic-brand jerseys are offered in several styles, including road, alternate, home, or batting practice-style jerseys. Youth-sized jerseys and personalized bathrobes are also available.

Additionally, SportsWorldChicago.com is offering free shipping on all customized jerseys.

"A personalized jersey is a great way to show you`re a Cubs fan, to treat the avid Cubs fan in your life, or to pay homage to former players," said Bradley Rosen, co-owner of Sports World.

This year, number 10 jerseys are expected to be popular, in honor of the late Cubs third baseman and celebrated WGN radio commentator Ron Santo.

"They`re probably the best thing you could ever get for a Cubs fan," said Rosen.

About SportsWorldChicago.com
SportsWorldChicago.com is the e-commerce website of the Sports World retail store, located at the corners of Clark and Addison Streets, across from Wrigley Field, Home of the Chicago Cubs. The website is a leading online retailer of affordably priced Chicago Cubs gear and apparel, as well as and other apparel and merchandise focused on Chicago sports and culture.

.help_desk.shipping-schedule.description:
Christmas Ordering Deadlines For U.S. Shipments

Please follow the ordering dated below to ensure your gifts arrive by December 24th. Shipping options apply to in-stock items shipped to a physical address within the U.S.A.

All of us at SportsWorldChicago.com appreciate your business. We are working hard to make sure that your holiday order arrives on time. Here are a few tips to help ease the stress of online holiday shopping.

  1. Order early: The sooner you place your order, the more time you have to allow for the shipment to arrive. Inventory stock status changes rapidly during the busy holiday season so you should allow time for possible back orders or product shortages.
  2. Watch for your package: During the holiday season we see a sharp increase in theft of packages after delivery. Due to the volume of packages we send, we are not able to require a signature for the package unless you specifically request it. It is best to have your package sent to work, a trusted neighbor, or any address where someone will be present at the time of delivery. Shipping insurance (nor our company) cover theft after the point of delivery.
  3. Inspect for damage: During the busy holiday period the likelihood of shipping damage increases because of the massive volume carried by shipping companies. Please make a quick inspection of your package and check for damage when it arrives. Notify us right away if you see any damage.

.in_the_news.big_z_autograph_signing_in_.meta_description: Big Z Autograph Signing in Wrigleyville
.in_the_news.big_z_autograph_signing_in_.page_title: Big Z Autograph Signing in Wrigleyville
.in_the_news.big_z_autograph_signing_in_.head_title: Big Z Autograph Signing in Wrigleyville
.in_the_news.big_z_autograph_signing_in_.description:
Share |

IMMEDIATE RELEASE

BIG Z AUTOGRAPH SIGNING IN WRIGLEYVILLE

CHICAGO (July 25, 2011) - In an effort to help the less fortunate, Wrigleyville Magazine is hosting an autograph signing with Chicago Cubs pitcher Carlos Zambrano. The event is on Friday, Aug, 5th immediately following the Cubs/Reds game and will be held at Sports World in Wrigleyville. Free and open to the public, the first 200 attendees who make a $30 donation to the Big Z Foundation will receive one autograph on an item of their choosing and the opportunity to have their picture taken with the one and only Big Z, along with a free Big Z Foundation T-shirt. Wristbands for the event will be sold for $30 on a first come, first serve basis beginning Monday, July 25th at Sports World and online at http://www.SportsWorldChicago.com/product/BIGZ/Biz-Z-Foundation-Autograph-Session-August-5th-2011.html and will hold a place in line on the day of the signing.

SportsWorld is located on the corner of Clark and Addison at 3555 N. Clark Street, across from the Wrigley Field marquee. Additional T-shirts may be purchased for $30 and will be sold exclusively at Sports World through the day of the signing with 100% of the proceeds from the event and T-shirt sales going to the Carlos Zambrano Foundation, Inc. Zambrano started the 501(c)(3) non-profit corporation, also known as the Big Z Foundation, to help serve underprivileged children and families in Chicago and around the world, especially those with educational obstacles and health issues.

"Helping children in Chicago has always been close to my heart as it is a way to give back to my fans that have always been good to me," said Zambrano, "Doing this event will give The Big Z Foundation an opportunity to continue its mission of helping children in the areas of education and health." According to Tim O`Riley, editor-in-chief of Wrigleyville Magazine, "I think that Mr. Zambrano is often portrayed by the media in a negative way but we at Wrigleyville Magazine know that he`s a very caring and generous man so we are absolutely thrilled to be a part of this fundraising event."

Wrigleyville Magazine is a free online publication written by Cubs fans for Cubs fans. It is published once a month during baseball season and during special events such as Spring Training. Fan-friendly to download and pass around - it features places to eat, drink, and shop, as well as things to see and do around Wrigleyville. Each issue also provides discounts from local merchants to help fans save money while still having fun.

.in_the_news.cubworldcom_unveils_new_rew.page_title: SportsWorldChicago.com Unveils New Rewards Program - January 26, 2011
.in_the_news.cubworldcom_unveils_new_rew.head_title: SportsWorldChicago.com Unveils New Rewards Program - January 26, 2011
.in_the_news.cubworldcom_unveils_new_rew.description:
Share |

IMMEDIATE RELEASE

SportsWorldChicago.com UNVEILS NEW REWARDS PROGRAM

SportsWorldChicago.com now giving fans more bang for their buck with new customer rewards program--good for Cubs, Blackhawks and Bears merchandise.

CHICAGO, January 26, 2011 - Online baseball sports retailer SportsWorldChicago.com is giving fans even more for their dollar with their new online Rewards Program.

Customers earn one point for every dollar spent on merchandise at SportsWorldChicago.com and other SportsWorld family retail sites, including ChiTownFootball.com and BlackhawksShop.com. After signing into their user account and making a purchase, points are earned. Accrued rewards points never expire and can be redeemed for jerseys, hats, t-shirts, children`s apparel, and more.

"The two things we`ve built our business on are the Cubs and Cubs fans," said SportsWorld partner Bradley Rosen. "Giving them a little something extra just for being a fan is our way of supporting their dedication to the team."

Rewards Program members also get premium access to sales, clearance merchandise, and opportunities to earn bonus points.

SportsWorld has cemented its place as a Chicago cornerstone for sportswear, both online and at its SportsWorld storefront at Clark Street and Addison Street. SportsWorld`s Wrigley Field webcam, featuring a live-streaming view on the Cubs' home base, has enjoyed heavy traffic locally, nationally, and internationally.

With the 2011 baseball season just over two months away, fans are encouraged to stock up on gear to show their loyalty to the North Side team.

"We just want to give our customers the newest and best," said Rosen. "It`s going to be a great season."

About SportsWorldChicago.com
SportsWorldChicago.com is the e-commerce website of the Sports World retail store, located at the corners of Clark and Addison Streets, across from Wrigley Field, Home of the Chicago Cubs. The website is a leading online retailer of affordably priced Chicago Cubs gear and apparel, as well as and other apparel and merchandise focused on Chicago sports and culture.

You've got the jersey, the hat, the blanket and even the   foam finger - now it's time to get some Chicago Cubs baseball tickets! You can buy Chicago Cubs tickets right here at SportsWorldChicago.com using our secure and easy online ordering system.




But that's not all - you can purchase tickets for other games in the American and National League, too. We have tickets for every one of the Major League Baseball teams; just search by region including East, Central and West.



  
Once you've selected the team you'd like to see play, you will be presented with the dates, venues and times of the available games. We even sell Cubs rooftop tickets! You can select your seat using the color-coded seating chart that accompanies each stadium's description; it's that easy.



  
When it comes to finding Cubs ticket brokers, there's no need to look any further than SportsWorldChicago.com. While you're here, be sure to check out the rest of our site and see if there's any team merchandise that you'd like to stock up on before you attend the game. We offer a $4.95 flat-rate standard shipping fee on all orders.

.careers.description:

In-Store Sales Associate - Summer 2013
Location: Chicago, Illinois
Posted / Update: 8/10/2012
Job Status: Paid Summer Sales Job
Job Length: April - October

Description:

A Sales Associate is responsible for maintaining outstanding customer service, generating sales and safeguarding company assets.

Primary Responsibilities:

  • Ensure that each customer receives outstanding service by providing a friendly environment, which includes greeting and acknowledging every customer, maintaining solid product knowledge and all other aspects of customer service
  • Assist in floor moves, merchandising, display maintenance, and housekeeping
  • Assist in processing and replenishing merchandise and monitoring floor stock
  • Aid customers in locating merchandise
  • Communicate customer requests to management
  • Assist in completing price changes within the department
  • Assist in ringing up sales at registers and/or bagging merchandise
  • Any other tasks as assigned from time to time by any manager

Skills and Competencies:

  • Ability to communicate with associates and customers
  • Ability to read, count, and write

Requirements:

  • Physical ability to stand for extended periods, and to move and handle boxes of merchandise throughout the store, which entails lifting, and perform all functions as set forth above
  • Ability to work varied hours/days, including nights, weekends, and holidays as needed

Resume Submission Below

eCommerce Digital Marketing Internship - Summer 2013
Location: Chicago, Illinois
Posted / Update: 8/10/2012
Job Status: Unpaid Summer Internship

Description:

Our company is seeking a dedicated, organized, high-energy junior or senior student in college majoring in marketing / advertising / digital eCommerce for our eCommerce Digital Marketing. Preference for Summer 2011 internship opportunity for credit, but not required. This is a 8-10 week internship opportunity. You must be able to work 40 hours / week, with flexible hours. This internship opportunity will begin from the beginning of Jun and continue through the beginning of August.

This internship will provide a qualified candidate with the opportunity to gain hands-on experience working within a growing licensed sports apparel fan eCommerce shop with multiple growing web properties. If you are an original independent minded thinker, looking for a smaller company where you can be a 'cog that runs the system, not a cog in the system', this opportunity is for you!

The intern will be exposed to eCommerce marketing / advertising strategy, planning & analysis, web implementation & development and will be regularly exposed to our advertising agency. The primary position objectives include finding strategic ways of driving sales, profit & strategy of the online business through analysis and creativeness. This skill set would be useful to a student pursuing a career on either the client or agency side of any eCommerce business.

Our web properties include SportsWorldChicago.com, BlackhawksShop.com, ChiTownFootball.com, NYDugout.com, UltimateSportsStore.com and a few others.

Primary Responsibilities:

  • Provide support, review, analyze and recommendations for all on-line advertising initiatives, which may include online or social media, as well as eCommerce traffic-driving initiatives including paid search, affiliate, email and display.
  • Support manager "exploring untapped opportunities" in development of eCommerce strategies
  • Affiliate and paid search channel monitoring
  • Determine and deliver strategies to promote the brand through a variety of tactics including SEM, SEO, email marketing, direct marketing, and online and social media
  • Strategize and enhance current social media initiatives
  • Regular research on media industry trends as well our competitive landscape
  • Coordination of e-mail campaigns
  • Affiliate Chain Newsletter creation
  • On-line advertising budget management, analysis and efficiencies
  • Researching new paid media opportunities and technologies
  • Provide technical, operational and creative direction to offer a best-in-class consumer site experience

Requirements:

  • Tremendous curiosity and drive towards "what's next", the ability to anticipate trends.
  • Advertising / Marketing major with background or emphasis in eCommerce
  • Excellent writing and organization skills
  • Strong computer skills, with knowledge of MS Office programs
  • Proven ability to work independently and multi-task
  • Creative, Self-Motivated & pro-active
  • Detail oriented & resourceful
  • Basic understanding of AdWords, YSM, Facebook advertising, Amazon product ads & Google Analytic
Resume Submission Below

This job description is not meant to be an all inclusive list of duties and responsibilities, but constitutes a general definition of the position's scope and function in the company.

SportsWorld is an equal opportunity employer.

If you are interested in this opportunity, please attach your cover letter and resume below, and be sure to complete the resume falsification form below.

.size_chart.description:
Sizing Tips
Use these tips as a general guide when finding your measurements:
  1. Chest/Bust: With your arms at your sides, measure around the fullest part of your chest, across shoulder blades and under arms.
  2. Waist: To measure your natural waistline, wrap the tape so it intersects your navel. Keep tape flat, but comfortably loose.
  3. Hips: Stand with your heels together and measure the fullest part of your hips, keeping the measuring tape level and parallel to the floor, front, and back.
  4. Inseam: Stand up straight, and start tape measure high in your crotch. Straighten the tape down the inside of your leg to the top of your shoe/foot.

.in_the_news.sports_world___s_online_sto.description:
Share |

IMMEDIATE RELEASE

SPORTS WORLD'S ONLINE STORE CUBWORLD.COM CHANGES NAME

CHICAGO, November 9, 2011 - Longtime Chicago sports merchandise retailer Sports World has changed the name of its online store, CubWorld.com, to SportsWorldChicago.com.

"Our Wrigleyville store has always been Sports World," said owner Bradley Rosen. "We`ve been here a long time, and now it`s time to bring a better connection between the neighborhood store and the online store."

While Sports World primarily stocks Chicago Cubs fan gear, both the physical store and the online store carry a selection of Chicago Bears, Blackhawks and Bulls sports memorabilia. The brick and mortar store has been at its location across the street from Wrigley Field, 3555 N. Clark St., since 1988.

"We love all Chicago sports, so the name change really reflects everything we have here," Rosen said."We're part of the Cubs community, but we`re also part of the Chicago sports community."

Beyond just Chicago sports merchandise, SportsWorldChicago.com`s inventory also includes fan gear for all NFL and MLB teams.

"We always love Chicago," Rosen said, "but we`re big sports fans, all around."

About SportsWorldChicago.com
SportsWorldChicago.com is the e-commerce website of the Sports World retail store, located at the corners of Clark and Addison Streets, across from Wrigley Field, Home of the Chicago Cubs. The leading online retailer of affordably priced Chicago sports gear and apparel, SportsWorldChicago.com is also home of the Wrigley Field Cam.

.in_the_news.cubworld_shows_northwestern.description:
Share |

IMMEDIATE RELEASE

SportsWorld SHOWS NORTHWESTERN SUPPORT AT WRIGLEY FIELD
Wrigley Field Marquee marquee goes purple for Allstate Wrigleyville Classic

CHICAGO, IL, November 15th, 2010 - The famous Wrigley Field marquee has gotten into the collegiate spirit.

In honor of the Nov. 20 Allstate Wrigleyville Classic college football game between the Northwestern Wildcats and the Illinois Fighting Illini, the 76-year-old Wrigley Field marquee is the recipient of a temporary makeover: a fresh coat of Wildcat purple paint.

The painted marquee can be viewed online via SportsWorldChicago.com`s Wrigley Field Cam, located at the corner of Clark and Addison streets. Originally, the marquee was painted a teal color, and later painted its signature red.

No college football game has been played at Wrigley Field since 1938 - two years after the marquee was installed.

"Events like this is why the Wrigley Field Cam is important to Chicago," said Brad Rosen, SportsWorld partner. "People can be a part of the action, and it`ll be fun to see the painting process as it goes along."

SportsWorldChicago.com also installed the Wrigleyville Bar Cam onto its Sports World storefront location earlier this month. The Bar Cam features a southeast view of Clark Street and many popular neighborhood watering holes.

"We`ve had tremendous support and good words about the webcams," Rosen said. "The site`s gotten hits from all over the world, and that`s what it`s about - showing off our neighborhood in Chicago."

Tickets for the Allstate Wrigleyville Classic have been on sale since August. Currently, limited view only tickets are available to the public.

About SportsWorldChicago.com

SportsWorldChicago.com is the e-commerce website of the Sports World retail store, located at the corners of Clark and Addison Streets, across from Wrigley Field, Home of the Chicago Cubs. The website is a leading online retailer of affordably priced Chicago Cubs gear and apparel, as well as and other apparel and merchandise focused on Chicago sports and culture.

=Baseball Sweatshirts - Cubs Sweatshirts for Men=

We`ve got the men`s baseball sweatshirts you need to show your Cubs and Wrigley Field pride.  Choose a baseball hooded sweatshirt or a zip-up or pullover in all men`s favorite colors.  If you need a larger size men`s Chicago Cubs sweatshirt, we`ve even got select items available in sizes up to 3X! .in_the_news.wrigleyville_retailer_sport.description:
Share |

IMMEDIATE RELEASE

Wrigleyville Retailer Sports World Chicago Enhances Online Experience

Neighborhood sports retailer Sports World Chicago evolves brand online with redesigned website offering exclusive Chicago Cubs and Chicago sports merchandise.

CHICAGO, May 2, 2012 - With baseball season under way, Chicago Cubs fans stop into longtime Wrigleyville staple, Sports World Chicago, for Cubs apparel and fan gear. But for Chicago sports fans unable to make it to Wrigley Field, Sports World`s online store, SportsWorldChicago.com, has undergone a redesign for better browsing.

Navigation has been streamlined for more intuitive organization. Users are able to find specific merchandise without hassle. "It really improves the whole experience of the site," Bradley Rosen, Sports World Chicago partner, said.

SportsWorldChicago.com`s e-commerce portion also received a remodel for improved purchasing speed. "We needed checkout to be just as easy as browsing," Rosen said.

Rosen sees the site redesign as an evolution of the Sports World Chicago brand. Founded in 1988 as CubWorld, the 3555 N. Clark St. store has seen a few changes along the way, including a name change in late 2011. Coming up, Rosen says, Sports World will continue to improve its online presence.

"Our online store`s just as important as our brick and mortar store, so we needed to make it just as great," Rosen said. "It`s all to keep up with our fans in Chicago and around the world."

About SportsWorldChicago.com
SportsWorldChicago.com is the e-commerce website of the Sports World retail store, located at the corners of Clark and Addison Streets, across from Wrigley Field, Home of the Chicago Cubs. The leading online retailer of affordably priced Chicago sports gear and apparel, SportsWorldChicago.com is also home of the Wrigley Field Cam.

.in_the_news.mporia.meta_description: Sports Retailer SportsWorld Launches Mobile Shopping Website with mPoria Inc.
.in_the_news.mporia.description:
Sports Retailer SportsWorld Launches Mobile Shopping Website with mPoria Inc.

Sports fans dial-up major league deals on their cell phones

CHICAGO, IL., Feb. 6, 2008 (BUSINESSWIRE) Ã¢ÂÂ Mobile commerce technology leader mPoria, Inc., and SportsWorld, a retailer specializing in Chicago Cubs and other major professional sports apparel and accessories, announced today the launch of Ã¢ÂÂSportsWorld.mobiÃ¢ÂÂ Ã¢ÂÂ a new mobile commerce website where sports fans can shop for their favorite sports merchandise using any cell phone or wireless device.

The site represents SportsWorldÃ¢ÂÂs first direct-to-consumer commerce initiative on the mobile Internet and is a sports fanÃ¢ÂÂs dream retail destination, offering a full line of sports apparel and accessories.ÃÂ  The company used mPoriaÃ¢ÂÂs GoMobile! m-commerce service to design and launch the m-commerce site in less than a week for under $200.ÃÂ 

According to Bradley Rosen, partner of SportsWorld, Ã¢ÂÂWith changing consumer behaviors, which are tied to evolving technologies, itÃ¢ÂÂs no longer enough [for a retailer] to stay competitive with just a storefront and flashy e-commerce site.ÃÂ  TodayÃ¢ÂÂs shoppers expect to be able to satisfy their retail appetite whenever they wish.ÃÂ  By adding a mobile component to our distribution strategy weÃ¢ÂÂre able to stay ahead of customer expectations and give them the flexibility and convenience of 24X7 shopping right from the palm of their hand.Ã¢ÂÂÃÂ 

To shop, users simply enter http://SportsWorld.mobi into their phoneÃ¢ÂÂs web browser.ÃÂ  Once on the site users can browse and shop.ÃÂ  Product information, including detailed descriptions, prices, and photos load very quickly and are presented in a user-friendly fashion. The checkout process is analogous to purchasing on the World Wide Web, with payment methods that include credit card, debit card and PayPal.ÃÂ  Once a shopper inputs their preferred shipping details that information is automatically saved for easy access when they shop the future.

mPoriaÃ¢ÂÂs CEO and co-founder Dan Wright commented, "With the growing popularity of the mobile web, an increasing number of traditional brick-and-mortar and online retailers are recognizing the importance and financial upside of multi-channel sales models that include m-commerce.ÃÂ  Mobile commerce in particular represents a $63 million opportunity and weÃ¢ÂÂre pleased to partner with industry leading retailers like SportsWorld to capitalize on it."

About SportsWorldChicago.com
Founded in 2000, SportsWorldChicago.com offers a large selection of Chicago Cubs, Wrigley Field, Chicago Bears, Hawks and Bulls merchandise, apparel, caps and gifts.ÃÂ  The SportsWorldChicago.com selection can be viewed at www.SportsWorldChicago.com or by calling one of SportsWorldChicago.comÃ¢ÂÂs product specialists at 888-4-SportsWorld (888-428-2967).

About mPoria, Inc.
mPoria Inc. is the leading provider of mobile commerce solutions in North America. The company builds and markets m-commerce stores for retailers and service providers, enabling them to extend their reach to the mobile channel and increase consumer sales.ÃÂ  Retail customers include GameStop, Buy.com, Hickory Farms, TicketsNow, Cutter & Buck, and others. Wireless carrier partners include Verizon Wireless, Sprint and AT&T.ÃÂ  mPoria is privately owned and based in Seattle, WA. For more information email or visit the companyÃ¢ÂÂs website at www.mporia.com.

.in_the_news.cubworld_webcam.desc:
=IMMEDIATE RELEASE=




===New Wrigley Field Web Cam: Game Day Experience, Minus Heartache====








CHICAGO, IL, July 21, 2010 - [[CubWorld.com]:popup=http://www.cubworld.com] has recently added a newly upgraded live-streaming Wrigley Field web cam [[Wrigley Field web cam]:popup=http://www.cubworld.com/category/a_cubworld_cam/] to their website. Perched at CubWorld.com`s brick & mortar location, Sports World, which is located at the SE corner of Clark & Addison, the camera provides a full 24-hour view of the front entrance of the ballpark and a live feed of all the action.
















The web cam also includes the ability to zoom in on the picture as well as scan side to side and up and down, for a more intimate view of the popular Wrigleyville corner. Fans can visit the [[web cam page]:popup=http://www.cubworld.com/category/a_cubworld_cam/]on the day of a game to check traffic, weather, crowd level, or just to get a taste of the action when an actual trip there isn`t possible. Oh, the stories it would tell if this camera could only talk.
















The only live web cam currently in Wrigleyville, the addictively voyeuristic feature has already become a hit with customers of CubWorld.com and Cubs fans in general, already garnering almost 600 "likes" on Facebook. There is even currently talk of sound being added to the camera, hopefully before the end of the 2010 season.
























===About CubWorld.com===








[[CubWorld.com]:popup=http://www.cubworld.com] is the e-commerce website of the Sports World retail store, located at the corners of Clark and Addison Streets, across from Wrigley Field, Home of the Chicago Cubs. The website is a leading online retailer of affordably priced Chicago Cubs gear and apparel, as well as other apparel and merchandise focused on Chicago sports and culture.

IMMEDIATE RELEASE

SportsWorldChicago.com Reacts to Trade Rumors, Fans Reap the Benefits

CHICAGO, IL, July 20, 2010 - Rumors abound regarding the future of many Chicago Cubs players, particularly Ted Lilly, Derrek Lee, Kosuke Fukudome, and Aramis Ramirez. Always ones to join in the fun of Cubs fan misery, SportsWorldChicago.com has reacted to these rumors - with a sale on these famous Cubs` jerseys.

At a cool $84.95, this is the lowest any authentic Chicago Cubs jersey will ever go during an active baseball season. Some fans are enjoying the gamble of purchasing a possibly soon-to-be-outdated jersey, while other feedback has shown that some fans like the obscurity of sporting a defunct Cub`s name on their back.

The rare low price also presents an opportunity to get oneself or a loved one any authentic baseball jersey, especially if it`s a purchase normally saved for after the piggy bank`s broken. Whether Lee, Lilly, Fukudome, or Ramirez are on or off the team in 2011, fans can have a high quality jersey that shows "I was there when..."

While SportsWorldChicago.com always touts a wide selection of Chicago Cubs apparel, accessories, and gifts, all at competitive prices, the rumor-guided sale displays a sense of humor about and understanding for what it is to be a lifelong Cubs fan.

About SportsWorldChicago.com

SportsWorldChicago.com is the e-commerce website of the Sports World retail store, located at the corners of Clark and Addison Streets, across from Wrigley Field, Home of the Chicago Cubs. The website is a leading online retailer of affordably priced Chicago Cubs gear and apparel, as well as and other apparel and merchandise focused on Chicago sports and culture.

.in_the_news.cubworldcom_puts_the_eye_on.description:
Share |

IMMEDIATE RELEASE

SportsWorldChicago.com Puts the Eye on Wrigleyville with New Bar Web Cam

CHICAGO, IL, November 5th, 2010 - Chicago`s Wrigleyville neighborhood is home to the Chicago Cubs, sports fanatics, rooftop bleachers, and a vivacious bar scene. Now, with the launch of SportsWorldChicago.com`s Wrigleyville Bar Cam, anyone can experience the lively high-jinks and plentiful pitchers of beer inside some of the neighborhood`s busiest sports bars.

"The Wrigleyville Bar Cam is a great way for everyone to see what`s going on in the neighborhood," said Brad Rosen, a partner at SportsWorld. "There`s always something happening on Clark."

Facing south on Clark Street, the camera provides a landscape scope of bar and restaurant happenings, including a clear view on local establishments such as Sluggers, Cubby Bear, Vines on Clark, Goose Island, Moe`s Cantina, Salt & Pepper Diner, and Mullen`s on Clark, among others. "It`s an exciting view of Chicago," Rosen said.

SportsWorld already operates the Wrigley Field Cam, which has captured the ongoings at Wrigley Field from Clark and Addison Streets since early 2008.

The Wrigleyville Bar Cam is attached to SportsWorldChicago.com`s Sports World store location at 3555 N. Clark Street. The storefront is currently in the midst of a 1,500 square foot expansion, set for completion in March 2011.

Visit the Wrigleyville Bar Cam on SportsWorld`s website, www.SportsWorldChicago.com.

About SportsWorldChicago.com

SportsWorldChicago.com is the e-commerce website of the Sports World retail store, located at the corners of Clark and Addison Streets, across from Wrigley Field, Home of the Chicago Cubs. The website is a leading online retailer of affordably priced Chicago Cubs gear and apparel, as well as other apparel and merchandise focused on Chicago sports and culture.

.holiday_shipping.description:
Christmas Ordering Deadlines For U.S. Shipments

Please follow the ordering dated below to ensure your gifts arrive by December 24th. Shipping options apply to in-stock items shipped to a physical address within the U.S.A.

All of us at SportsWorldChicago.com appreciate your business. We are working hard to make sure that your holiday order arrives on time. Here are a few tips to help ease the stress of online holiday shopping.


  1. Order Early: The sooner you place your order, the more time you have to allow for the shipment to arrive. Inventory stock status changes rapidly during the busy holiday season so you should allow time for possible back orders or product shortages.
  2. Watch for Your Package: During the holiday season we see a sharp increase in theft of packages after delivery. Due to the volume of packages we send, we are not able to require a signature for the package unless you specifically request it. It is best to have your package sent to work, a trusted neighbor, or any address where someone will be present at the time of delivery. Shipping insurance (nor our company) cover theft after the point of delivery.
  3. Inspect for Damage: During the busy holiday period the likelihood of shipping damage increases because of the massive volume carried by shipping companies. Please make a quick inspection of your package and check for damage when it arrives. Notify us right away if you see any damage.

Don't miss your chance to see your Chicago Cubs LIVE! Buy your Chicago Cubs tickets now!
.aa.chicago_cubs_tickets.description2:
Chicago Cubs information,

There are few teams that can rival the spirit and history of the Chicago Cubs.; The Boys in Blue are one of two MLB clubs based in Chicago. Established in 1870, the organization is one of two original members of the Central Division of MLB's National League. Purchasing Chicago Cubs tickets not only offers fans a chance to see big name players vie for a win, they also get to marvel at Wrigley Field, one of the oldest ballparks in the nation with a beautiful view of Lake Michigan as the backdrop.

The Chicago Cubs have been playing in the Midwest city of Chicago since their inception. Known by a few different team monikers, the Cubbies have been sporting their present team name since 1902. Playing on the grounds of their beloved Wrigley Field, the stadiums location on Chicagos north side is the basis for the teams The North Siders nickname.

Though the team has a storied history, it's also one that's been full of ups and downs. Between 1908 and 2012, the Cubs did not win a single World Series title, and they often lost in heartbreaking fashion. Despite the disappointment, the Cubs fan base is among the league's most loyal.

Cubs fans are diehard. With the team possessing the infamous record of not having won a championship over a period of more than 100 years, one cannot be a fair-weather fan. Regardless of the teams tournament baseball rankings, the Chicago Cubs have produced a number of Hall of Fame Baseball players. In 2007 the Cubbies made an incredible turnaround from worst to first under then new manager Lou Piniella, giving fans a glimmer of hope. Unfortunately the team made an early exit in the first round of the playoffs in a three game sweep.

In true baseball fashion, nothing would be complete without a few contentions; step up to the plate St. Louis Cardinals, Milwaukee Brewers and the cross-town Chicago White Sox. In 2010 the Chicago Cubs beat rival team Milwaukee Brewers at Wrigley on opening day. The sweet victory of the smaller battles won.

The Cubs once rivaled the Boston Red Sox for having both one of the oldest ballparks in the U.S., and the longest World Series drought. With the Sox taking home the title in 2004 and again in 2007, it seems like the time has come for the Cubs to do the same. Having such a weight hanging over the team's heads might make it even more exciting to see them play live, since they have so much to prove to fans and other teams alike.

Whether they are on the top or somewhere well below the surface, the Cubbies are on a quest to give their fans a historic baseball first the breaking of the teams unlucky record. Dont miss a game because you just might be missing the start of a new Cubs era. Get your Chicago Cubs baseball tickets today and perhaps your Cubs World Series tickets will be just around the corner!

Stay in the know with Chicago Cubs scores and news from SportsWorldChicago.com. As an official retailer of merchandise for the much-loved Chicago Cubs, we thought it would be helpful to provide our customers and fans with up-to-date Cubs news, stats and information about the  Chicago Cubs.


Whether you're looking for the latest stats or news about the Chicago Cubs, you will find everything you ever wanted to know right here. From time-sensitive information on the current game to the top MLB news headlines, we've got you covered. You will even find MLB statistics including scores and matchups, injuries, teams, players, standings and odds.


While you're here, be sure to check out our great selection of Cubs merchandise including official team jerseys, hats, blankets, sweatshirts, jackets, accessories, souvenirs and much more. We offer a flat-rate shipping fee of $4.95 on all orders so purchasing sporting merchandise from us is always affordable. We even offer Cubs-themed merch for infants and toddlers - because you can never be too young to be a Cubs fan!

.holiday_shipping.schedule.description:
Christmas Ordering Deadlines For U.S. Shipments

Please follow the ordering dated below to ensure your gifts arrive by December 24th. Shipping options apply to in-stock items shipped to a physical address within the U.S.A.

All of us at SportsWorldChicago.com appreciate your business. We are working hard to make sure that your holiday order arrives on time. Here are a few tips to help ease the stress of online holiday shopping.


  1. Order early: The sooner you place your order, the more time you have to allow for the shipment to arrive. Inventory stock status changes rapidly during the busy holiday season so you should allow time for possible back orders or product shortages.
  2. Watch for your package: During the holiday season we see a sharp increase in theft of packages after delivery. Due to the volume of packages we send, we are not able to require a signature for the package unless you specifically request it. It is best to have your package sent to work, a trusted neighbor, or any address where someone will be present at the time of delivery. Shipping insurance (nor our company) cover theft after the point of delivery.
  3. Inspect for damage: During the busy holiday period the likelihood of shipping damage increases because of the massive volume carried by shipping companies. Please make a quick inspection of your package and check for damage when it arrives. Notify us right away if you see any damage.

.rewards_program.terms___conditions.description3:
=Terms and Conditions=
===Point Redemption===


All points can only be redeemed at SportsWorld unless otherwise specified by SportsWorld. All qualified SportsWorld reward members will accrue a point for every approved dollar spent.  The amount of points awarded per dollar spent is determined solely by SportsWorld, who reserves the right to change the value of the points at any time. Purchases prior to your sign up date are not retroactive and will not be applied to your rewards account.  All points are accrued will not have an expiration date.  Accrued rewards points may be used for any product on SportsWorld.  All rewards redemption's are subject to availability.  The rewards customer will be notified if the item they have on order is no longer available or back-ordered.  If an item is back-ordered a customer service representative will notify the customer with the time it will become available.  At this point, the customer may choose to cancel or wait for the product.  Items ordered at the same time may arrive separately on different days.  SportsWorld may run special rewards programs that are available during specified time periods.  These will be subject to the terms and conditions specifically applied to them.  Redeemed rewards are not replaceable, exchangeable, refundable or transferable for cash.



===Important Notice===

SportsWorld reserves the right to change the membership rewards program terms and conditions at any time.  This may include, but is not limited to, the number points earned for spending, the number of points required to redeem rewards, or any caps or fees on earning and redeeming points.  SportsWorld may cancel the program, as well as any point balances by giving 60 days prior notice by email.  If the email is not received due to a spam blocker, a change of email address, a full mailbox or any other reason, SportsWorld will not be held responsible and will not be required to extend the notification time.


Points will not be applied unless you:


* Sign into your user account during checkout so that we can associate your order with your points account, or
* You call in to place your order and let the Customer Service Representative know that you have a rewards account and give them the email address you used to start the account
In the event that a rewards member`s method of payment is declined, points will not be earned. Points are not earned until the transaction is completed and paid in full.


Points accrued by rewards members are not transferable by operation of law or otherwise to any person or entity and cannot be transferred to any other account.


Credits posted to orders that acquired rewards points, including those arising from returned goods or services will also post a debit to the points accrued in your rewards account.


Rewards points are NOT eligible towards the purchase of tickets on SportsWorld or any of our affiliate sites.


SportsWorld reserves the right to decline any request to convert reward points for purchase at any time.

----
===Point Accrual===

SportsWorld rewards points may be accrued on orders placed directly through any SportsWorld family sites (including WrigleyFieldShop.com, ChiTownFootball.com, BlackhawksShop.com, and more) only. Orders placed through partner sites, such as Shop.com, Buy.com, Amazon.com, etc, are not eligible for points.

Credits posted to orders that acquired Rewards points, including those arising from returned goods or services will also post a debit to the points accrued in your rewards account.

Rewards points are NOT eligible towards the purchase of tickets on SportsWorldChicago.com or any of our affiliate sites.

----
===Eligibility===

All customers must have a valid physical address, email address and phone number in order to participate in our rewards programs.
----
===Shipping===

Reward points cannot be used for specialty shipping services.  Specialty shipping services is defined as any delivery beyond curbside of your home.  Reward points can only be used for standard delivery: curbside for freight items, and front door for UPS, FedEx and USPS.  Any upgraded shipping (specialty shipping services, express delivery, etc.) will be paid for separately by another method of payment.

----
===Returns===

Please call us at 1-888-428-2967 to resolve any reward redemption return issues.  Rewards points are not redeemable towards return shipping costs. Damaged or defective items must be returned within 30 days of delivery once that return has been approved.  All customers must advise a customer service representative if a replacement is required.  All items must be unused and returned in the original package.


All packages must be returned to: SportsWorldChicago.com, 3555 N. Clark St, Chicago, IL, 60657, unless otherwise instructed by a SportsWorld customer service representative at the time of acquisition of a return authorization number.


SportsWorld reserves the right to modify or cancel any reward at any time.

----
===Reward Members Cancellation===

In the event that the participating rewards member becomes unreachable via email or telephone number, we may deactivate and cancel the members points and rewards program membership at any time.  If a rewards membership is cancelled due to death or insolvency, any points accrued in the rewards account may be forfeited.

----
===Taxes===

Applicable taxes are not eligible to be paid with rewards points. The rewards member is responsible for all taxes and / or levies that may apply. Shipments to the state of Illinois are subject to 9.5% tax.

----
===Fraud===

Fraud or abuse relating to the accrual of your rewards points, or redemption of your rewards points, may result in forfeiture of your accrued points and cancellation of your rewards account.

----
===General Terms===

All questions regarding eligibility, accrual, conversion and/or redemption will be resolved at our sole discretion.  We are not responsible for any typographical errors, including, but not limited to: product descriptions, pricing, required points and photographic images.  We reserves the right to make corrections and adjustments to reward members accounts in the event of a price change.


The terms and conditions are governed by and construed under the laws of Illinois.

----
===Arbitration===

To terms that are set forth, claim means any claim, dispute or controversy between the rewards member and SportsWorld that may arise in which the circumstances and procedures under which claims may be arbitrated instead of litigated in court.

----
===Gift Certificates and Gift Cards===

Rewards members who purchase gift certificates or gift cards are eligible to acquire points, not the person redeeming them.

----
===Corporate Accounts===

Corporate accounts may purchase large quantity of points for employee programs.  These accounts can be set up with our sales department, who will work individually with all corporate accounts to create a program that caters to each company`s specific needs.


Rewards points are NOT eligible towards the purchase of tickets on SportsWorld or any of our affiliate sites.

.in_the_news.sports_world_announces_onli.description:
Share |

IMMEDIATE RELEASE

Sports World Announces Online Custom Apparel Shop

Longtime Chicago sports merchandise retailer Sports World has developed a simple tool that helps people design their own apparel at their website, SportsWorldChicago.com.

CHICAGO, January 18, 2013 - Longtime Chicago sports merchandise retailer Sports World has developed a simple tool that helps people design their own apparel at their website, SportsWorldChicago.com.

“Designing t-shirts and accessories for events, rec league teams and plain old fun needed to be easier,” said owner Bradley Rosen. “This tool makes the whole process quick and simple.”

Sports World has variety of t-shirts, sweatshirts and other apparel for men, women, children and infants that can be customized. The wide variety can accommodate any style. Customers can finish their custom apparel design in less than 10 minutes.

The custom tool works easily to customize a funny t-shirt for a party or a 200-person conference because they require only 24 items as the minimum order. Sports World’s competitive prices and free shipping on all orders makes the process even easier.

Design options go beyond sports. Customers can upload their own images or choose between dozens of templates. In addition, the wide variety of fonts, colors and sizes give customers total freedom.

“We know Chicago is a city of teams.” Rosen said. “Whether it’s your team at work or a softball team on the weekends, Chicagoans rally around their group. And it always helps if you have a uniform.”

In addition to the new online tool, SportsWorldChicago.com and physical storefront at 3555 N. Clark St. still offers a complete inventory of professional sports apparel, accessories and merchandize.

Design your custom t-shirt or accessory with the new tool.

About SportsWorldChicago.com
SportsWorldChicago.com is the e-commerce website of the Sports World retail store, located at the corners of Clark and Addison Streets, across from Wrigley Field, Home of the Chicago Cubs. The leading online retailer of affordably priced Chicago sports gear and apparel, SportsWorldChicago.com is also home of the Wrigley Field Cam.

.chicago-cubs-jerseys.description:
=Authentic Chicago Cubs Home, Road, Alternate and Personalized jerseys==
If you ask us, no Cubs fan has a complete attire selection without an [[authentic Cubs jersey]:category=m_jerseys.men/].  And SportsWorldChicago.com is the perfect place to pick one up, whether you're looking for an adult or [[youth jersey]:category=m_jerseys.youth___child/] or an authentic, home, away or [[personalized jersey]:category=m_jerseys.custom/]. We carry a wide selection for fans to choose from, with a mix of current Cubs jerseys, as well as some throwback designs that pay homage to the Cubs of yesteryear.


At SportsWorldChicago.com, you have the option to personalize a Cubs jersey with your own name or to even customize it with your favorite player's name. You name it (get it?): Ryne Sandberg, Darwin Barney, Starlin Castro or Anthony Rizzo...Any Cubbie, any jersey style, totally your choice.


=Ordering Online & Size Questions=
If you would like to place an order for any of our Chicago Cubs jerseys, you can do so right here on our website. Our online shopping cart system makes it easy to enter in the details and size of your items. If you prefer, you can also make your purchase over the phone by giving us a call at 888.428.2967. One of our staff members will be able to help you and can answer any questions you might have about your order. 
 


If you're uncertain about what size to order for your new jersey, please check out our [[sizing chart]:popup=http://www.SportsWorldChicago.com/category/size_chart/?wrapper=~cw2_pop_theme].

.in_the_news.cubworld_expansion_press_re.description:
Share |

IMMEDIATE RELEASE

Sports World Expansion Expands Retail Haven for Cubs Fans

CHICAGO, IL, September 24, 2010 - Baseball retail staple SportsWorldChicago.com has begun construction to expand its longstanding Wrigleyville store, Sports World. Construction began on Sept. 5, 2010.

Adding 1,500 square feet to the retail outlet has been in the works "for a while," said partner Brad Rosen. "We`ve finally gotten it off the ground, and we`re excited to be able to expand and offer even more merchandise for fans."

Sports World, a retail mecca selling exclusive official gear for the Chicago Cubs baseball team, will remain open during construction. "It`s important for fans and customers to know we`re always here for them," Rosen said, "even if it`s not baseball season." Rosen expects construction on Sports World to be completed by March 2011.

The Sports World expansion is unrelated to the controversial Addison Park on Clark project that is being planned behind the store. While Sports World is right in the midst of that pending development, the retailer has no bearing on when or whether that project will be built.

Sports World, which operates SportsWorldChicago.com and online retailers BlackhawksShop.com, ChiTownFootball.com, and NYDugout.com, has been in business since 1988. Offering an ample selection of sports merchandise to fans is Sports World`s "ultimate goal," Rosen said.

Construction at Sports World`s 3555 N. Clark St. location and online at SportsWorldChicago.com only adds to the company`s enthusiastically pro-Chicago presence. "We want to make our store the ultimate Chicago Cubs store in the world," Rosen said.

View Our Expansion

About SportsWorldChicago.com

SportsWorldChicago.com is the e-commerce website of the Sports World retail store, located at the corners of Clark and Addison Streets, across from Wrigley Field, Home of the Chicago Cubs. The website is a leading online retailer of affordably priced Chicago Cubs gear and apparel, as well as other apparel and merchandise focused on Chicago sports and culture.

=Vintage Chicago Cubs Shirts=
With this great selection of vintage Cubs t-shirts and more, both men and women can enjoy the Chicago Cubs styles, logos and colors that have stood the test of time. You'll love the nostalgic feeling you get when you wear one of our high-quality, great looking vintage shirts from Majestic Athletic, 5th and Ocean Clothing and '47 Brand. The vintage style designs on these Cubs t-shirts reflect a rich history and a Chicago legacy that so many have enjoyed since the Cubbies began more than a century ago. Just like our hope stays alive through thick and thin, so will these vintage-style t-shirts! Be sure to also check out our larger collection of [[Chicago Cubs vintage shirts]:category=d_vintage/] and sweatshirts.

We will use this information only for the purpose of notifying you of specials and changes going on at SportsWorld. Emailings are done approximately twice per month, but may be greater depending upon the season and current specials at SportsWorld.
































































===LIMITATIONS OF LIABILITY:===
















Please note SportsWorld reserves the right at its sole discretion to cancel, terminate, modify or suspend the sweepstakes.

IMMEDIATE RELEASE

Sports World Chicago Earns Status as a Google Official Store

SportsWorldChicago.com granted elite status as an official Google Trusted Store

CHICAGO, August 1, 2012 - Online sports retailer SportsWorldChicago.com offers what many consider the best selection of sports apparel on the web. While online retailers can offer a good customer experience, few like SportsWorldChicago.com can earn the status as Google Trusted Store.

"Customer service is our number one priority," store partner Bradley Rosen said. "We want customers to feel confident throughout the entire buying process."

Google Trusted Stores, launched in October 2011, seeks to help shoppers find reliable online stores. If an online retailer meets the strict criteria of Google Trusted Stores, a badge is placed on the site to identify it. Customers are able to see information about the storeâs reputation for shipping and service based on number of transactions.

So far, a number of Google Trusted Store retailers have seen improved conversions on their sites.

"It lets shoppers know we`re here for them," Rosen said. "You can say you have fast shipping, but having a badge showing you do, gives customers confidence in your store."

Part of the longstanding Sports World store in Chicago`s Wrigleyville neighborhood, the SportsWorldChicago.com online sports store offers a variety of sports apparel, including Chicago Cubs merchandise and other MLB team shirts.

"It`s been great working with Google, and it gives us the chance to serve the sports fans out there even better," Rosen said. "Visit us online to see for yourself."

About SportsWorldChicago.com
SportsWorldChicago.com is the e-commerce website of the Sports World retail store, located at the corners of Clark and Addison Streets, across from Wrigley Field, Home of the Chicago Cubs. The leading online retailer of affordably priced Chicago sports gear and apparel, SportsWorldChicago.com is also home of the Wrigley Field Cam.

.a_g.description:
Cubs' Piniella to retire at end of season
July 20, 2010 1:17 PM | Chicago Tribune | UPDATED STORY

Lou Piniella wants to give the Cubs time to plan by announcing his plans to retire at season's end. (Phil Velasquez/Tribune)

By Paul Sullivan

Lou Piniella announced Tuesday he will retire at the end of the 2010 season, ending his four-year run in Chicago and his managerial career.

"I couldn't be more appreciative of the Cubs organization for providing me the opportunity to manage this ballclub,"ÃÂ Piniella said in a statement. "I've had four wonderful years here that I wouldn't trade for anything in the world.ÃÂ  I've grown to love the city and the fans but at my age (67 at the end of the season) it will be time to enter a new phase in my life.ÃÂ  It will enable me to spend more valuable time with my family -- my wife, my kids and my grandchildren.ÃÂ  God has blessed me to have been able to work this many years in the game that I love.

"Why make this announcement now? Jim Hendry asked me in recent weeks regarding my future with the team and I told him I had made the decision to retire at the end of the season. Since my decision has now been made, I don't want to mislead anyone about my intentions when asked in the future.

"But more importantly, announcing my decision now is what's best for this organization in the long run.ÃÂ  It gives Jim Hendry ample time to find the next manager and he doesn't need to do so in secrecy. The Cubs are one of the greatest organizations in baseball. I care very deeply for this organization and want nothing more than for it to experience present and long-term success. I'm proud of our accomplishments during my time here and this will be a perfect way for me to end my career.

"But let me make one thing perfectly clear: our work is far from over. I want to keep the momentum going more than anything else and win as many games as we can to get back in this pennant race.ÃÂ  I'm going to give every effort I have to help this team win and that will remain my sole focus through the rest of the season.:

The New York Daily News first reported Piniella's decision.

While Piniella gave hints that this would be his final year in an interview with two CubsÃÂ beat reporters two weeks ago in Phoenix, he maintained at that time that no final decision had been made, but that Chicago would be his final stop.

"I'm not going anymore," he said. "When I'm done here, I'm going home. I'm going to enjoy my family, enjoy my friends and do things I haven't been able to do for the past 50 years of my life. Im going to enjoy myself a little bit. I got myself a boat last year. It's sitting over there at the marina. My kids use it, which is good. But yeah, I'm not going anywhere. When I'm finished here, I'm going home and that's it."

Piniella's run in Chicago is unlikely to end on a good note, with his team out of contention and his goal of winning a championship unfulfilled. He has been criticized this year for lacking intensity and seeming remote on the bench.

"You know what, truthfully, the media's been very fair to me," he said in Phoenix. "I get some pot shots from time to time. But that's to be expected. But I've enjoyed this whole experience. I really have. And it's been a challenge. It hasn't been easy. This hasn't been easy. I was told coming in by some good friends that this would be an experience of a great magnitude. And they basically were right."

IMMEDIATE RELEASE

Wrigleyville Retailer Sports World Chicago Enhances Online Experience

Neighborhood sports retailer Sports World Chicago evolves brand online with redesigned website offering exclusive Chicago Cubs and Chicago sports merchandise.

CHICAGO, May 2, 2012 - With baseball season under way, Chicago Cubs fans stop into longtime Wrigleyville staple, Sports World Chicago, for Cubs apparel and fan gear. But for Chicago sports fans unable to make it to Wrigley Field, Sports World`s online store, SportsWorldChicago.com, has undergone a redesign for better browsing.

Navigation has been streamlined for more intuitive organization. Users are able to find specific merchandise without hassle. "It really improves the whole experience of the site," Bradley Rosen, Sports World Chicago partner, said.

SportsWorldChicago.com`s e-commerce portion also received a remodel for improved purchasing speed. "We needed checkout to be just as easy as browsing," Rosen said.

Rosen sees the site redesign as an evolution of the Sports World Chicago brand. Founded in 1988 as CubWorld, the 3555 N. Clark St. store has seen a few changes along the way, including a name change in late 2011. Coming up, Rosen says, Sports World will continue to improve its online presence.

"Our online store`s just as important as our brick and mortar store, so we needed to make it just as great," Rosen said. "It`s all to keep up with our fans in Chicago and around the world."

About SportsWorldChicago.com
SportsWorldChicago.com is the e-commerce website of the Sports World retail store, located at the corners of Clark and Addison Streets, across from Wrigley Field, Home of the Chicago Cubs. The leading online retailer of affordably priced Chicago sports gear and apparel, SportsWorldChicago.com is also home of the Wrigley Field Cam.

Cubs headgear is definitely way cooler than the headgear the orthodontist made you wear when you were 13 years old.  Just sayin`.  And with our wide selection of Cubs hats, caps, visors, and winter caps, the cool Cubs headgear options are aplenty. So many options, so many games-you might even get a few and never miss an occasion to root the northsiders on in style!


At SportsWorldChicago.com, we want to ensure that all of our customers are satisfied with the fit and feel of their new baseball hats from this great Chicago team. To make sure your new Cubs hat fits, please check out our [[sizing chart]:category=size_chart/?wrapper=~cw2_pop_theme].  If you have any questions about our selection of hats, and other Chicago Cubs apparel, simply give us a call at 888-428-2967. One of our team members will be more than happy answer any questions and process your order. Or just purchase your new Chicago Cubs cap right here online through our shopping cart system.
